fields.value: Reconstructed Precipitation and Temperature CFSv2 Forecasts for 2011-2018

dsDescriptionValue.value: Temperature and precipitation forecasts from operational CFSv2 (Climate Forecast System), for biweekly dates in 2011-2018, with a prediction window of 3-6 weeks and interpolated to a 1x1 grid containing the western contiguous United States.

publicationCitation.value: Hwang, J.; Orenstein, P.; Cohen, J.; Pfeiffer, K.; and Mackey, L. 2018. Improving Subseasonal Forecasting in the Western U.S. with Machine Learning.

fields.value: See "Improving Subseasonal Forecasting in the Western U.S. with Machine Learning" for details on dataset contents and construction.

value: Climate Forecast System (CFSv2) archived operational forecasts were retrieved from the National Center for Environmental Information (NCEI) site at https://nomads.ncdc.noaa.gov/modeldata/cfsv2_forecast_ts_9mon/.
